If you're thinking of taking a cruise and traveling solo, you probably
already know that cruise lines charge an extra fee for an individual
booking a cabin intended for two. Typically, the cruise line starts with
the per-person rate based on double occupancy and adds 50% to 100% to
the price for a single traveler -- the dreaded single supplement.<br>
<br>
The good news? Vacations To Go has found or negotiated low or no single
supplements on many prime cruise departures. These great solo deals are
updated daily and listed on our site.
<a href="https://www.vacationstogo.com/ticker.cfm?r=0&jpw=107&nr=cus_L0p_int&source=cruisemm&csp=L0pL0p&mmz=1&pdm=0">Click here</a>
to see our <b>Singles Discounts</b> ticker now.<br>
<br><hr><br><!-- End of intro -->
